This is very file will help you to update your linux system like macBook

Step 1: Download themes from gitgub and install one by one. Extract them and then in main folder there is bash file to install themes to run them type command: ./install.sh  (for each file seperatly)
      https://github.com/vinceliuice/WhiteSur-gtk-theme
      https://github.com/vinceliuice/WhiteSur-icon-theme
      https://github.com/vinceliuice/WhiteSur-cursors
      
Step 2: Donwload the Google chrome browser to integrate with gnome
Step 3: Install gnome extension on chrome Browser
Step 4: Run this bash file give: gnome.sh

Step 5: Search for tweaks in your applications. Open tweaks and under Extensions tab enable user Theme. 
Step 6:  In tweaks, in Appearance tab you have option to select installed themes. select the theme we have
        just install corresponding to shell, cursor and icons themes.
        
Finally, Your system is like macBook. If still not, Restart your system.


If you want to further customize your system. Access Gnome extensions and isntall extensions do you like just with single click.
        https://extensions.gnome.org/
        

Some famous and attractive gnome extesions
Dash to dock
unity
compiz alike magic lamp effect
Gsconnect
Media controls
Open weather
Net speed simplified
Time in date menu


      
      
